→Gauri and Lieberman, “Boundary Institutions and HIV/AIDS Policy.”<br />
→Richard Parker, “Building the Foundations for the Response to HIV/AIDS in Brazil: The Development of HIV/AIDS Policy, 1982–1996,” <em>Divulgação Em Saúde Para Debate</em>, no. 27 (2003): 143–83.</div></div><div class='single-reference'><div class='reference-title'>5</div><div class='reference-content'><img src="https://mk0itemsssrcorgqb419.kinstacdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/identity-crisis.jpg" /><span class="citation">Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press, 2019</span><span class="more-info"><a href="https://press.princeton.edu/books/hardcover/9780691174198/identity-crisis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">More Info →</a></span></div></div><div class='single-reference'><div class='reference-title'>6</div><div class='reference-content'><img src="https://mk0itemsssrcorgqb419.kinstacdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/deep-roots.jpg" /><span class="citation">Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press, 2008</span><span class="more-info"><a href="https://press.princeton.edu/books/hardcover/9780691176741/deep-roots" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">More Info →</a></span></div></div><div class='single-reference'><div class='reference-title'>7</div><div class='reference-content'>Questions we raise in Melani Cammett and Evan Lieberman, “<a href="https://ethics.harvard.edu/building-solidarity" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Building Solidarity: Challenges, Options, and Implications for Covid-19 Responses</a>,” COVID Rapid Response White Paper Series (Cambridge, MA, Harvard University, 2020).</div></div></div></div>							</div>
						</div>
							
							
							
												
								
